<section class="buying-guide">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Camera Pricing & Buying Guide</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Understanding camera types and specifications helps make informed decisions regardless of budget. This guide will demystify the technical jargon and help you find the perfect camera for your needs.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Camera Types Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h3 class="guide-section-title">Understanding Camera Types</h3>
      <div class="camera-types-grid">
        <div class="type-card">
          <div class="type-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/90946/pexels-photo-90946.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600" alt="DSLR Camera" />
          </div>
          <div class="type-header">
            <h4>DSLR Cameras</h4>
            <span class="type-badge">Traditional</span>
          </div>
          <p>Mirror mechanism with optical viewfinder, excellent battery life, and extensive lens ecosystem. Canon and Nikon lead this category with decades of lens compatibility.</p>
          <div class="type-features">
            <span class="feature">Optical Viewfinder</span>
            <span class="feature">Long Battery Life</span>
            <span class="feature">Extensive Lenses</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="type-card">
          <div class="type-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/247769/pexels-photo-247769.jpeg" alt="Mirrorless Camera" />
          </div>
          <div class="type-header">
            <h4>Mirrorless Cameras</h4>
            <span class="type-badge popular">Popular</span>
          </div>
          <p>Electronic viewfinder system, compact size, and growing lens selections. Sony dominates this space, with Canon, Nikon, and Fujifilm offering strong alternatives.</p>
          <div class="type-features">
            <span class="feature">Compact Size</span>
            <span class="feature">Electronic Viewfinder</span>
            <span class="feature">Growing Ecosystem</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="type-card">
          <div class="type-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/10910631/pexels-photo-10910631.jpeg" alt="Point and Shoot Camera" />
          </div>
          <div class="type-header">
            <h4>Point & Shoot</h4>
            <span class="type-badge">Convenient</span>
          </div>
          <p>Fixed lens convenience with automatic controls and portability focus. Canon PowerShot and Sony RX series lead this category for everyday photography.</p>
          <div class="type-features">
            <span class="feature">Fixed Lens</span>
            <span class="feature">Automatic Controls</span>
            <span class="feature">Ultra Portable</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Specialized Types Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h3 class="guide-section-title">Specialized Camera Types</h3>
      <div class="specialized-grid">
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/821651/pexels-photo-821651.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=400" alt="Medium Format Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>Medium Format</h4>
          <p>Larger sensor benefits for professional applications with higher costs. Fujifilm GFX and Hasselblad systems offer exceptional image quality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7206225/pexels-photo-7206225.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Action Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>Action Cameras</h4>
          <p>Built for durability, stabilization, and compact size. GoPro leads the market with DJI offering strong alternatives for extreme sports.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3657268/pexels-photo-3657268.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Drone Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>Drone Cameras</h4>
          <p>Aerial photography integration with regulation considerations. DJI dominates the consumer space with advanced stabilization systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6598819/pexels-photo-6598819.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="360 Degree Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>360Â° Cameras</h4>
          <p>Immersive content creation with specialized software needs. Insta360 and GoPro MAX excel in this emerging category.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/279906/pexels-photo-279906.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=400" alt="Film Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>Film Cameras</h4>
          <p>Analog appeal with ongoing film costs and learning curve. Mix of vintage options and new production models available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-card">
          <div class="spec-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/31158822/pexels-photo-31158822/free-photo-of-professional-camera-rig-with-lcd-display-in-studio.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Cinema Camera" />
          </div>
          <h4>Cinema Cameras</h4>
          <p>Professional video features with different priorities than stills. RED, Blackmagic, and Sony professional lines dominate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Specifications Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="specs-hero">
        <div class="specs-content">
          <h3 class="guide-section-title">Essential Specifications Decoded</h3>
          <p>Understanding key camera specifications helps you make informed decisions based on your specific photography needs and budget.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-image">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/51383/photo-camera-subject-photographer-51383.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600" alt="Camera Specifications" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="specs-table">
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">Sensor Size</div>
          <div class="spec-description">Affects crop factor, low light performance, and depth of field. Larger sensors generally perform better in challenging conditions.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">Megapixels</div>
          <div class="spec-description">More isn't always better. Consider your output needs - 24MP is excellent for most users, while 50MP+ suits large prints.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">ISO Range</div>
          <div class="spec-description">Balance between noise and sensitivity. Modern cameras perform well up to ISO 3200, with high-end models reaching ISO 25,600+.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">Autofocus System</div>
          <div class="spec-description">Phase detection vs contrast detection systems. More focus points and eye detection improve tracking performance.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">Image Stabilization</div>
          <div class="spec-description">In-body vs lens-based systems. IBIS (In-Body Image Stabilization) works with any lens, while lens-based is often more effective.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <div class="spec-name">Lens Mount</div>
          <div class="spec-description">Determines compatibility and future investment protection. Consider the ecosystem size and third-party support.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Evaluation Checklist -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h3 class="guide-section-title">What to Evaluate Before Buying</h3>
      <div class="evaluation-hero">
        <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/32203083/pexels-photo-32203083/free-photo-of-top-view-of-a-retro-style-digital-camera.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" alt="Camera Evaluation" />
      </div>
      <div class="evaluation-cards">
        <div class="eval-card">
          <h4>Physical Handling</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Grip comfort and button placement</li>
            <li>Menu navigation ease</li>
            <li>Weight and size considerations</li>
            <li>Weather sealing requirements</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="eval-card">
          <h4>Intended Use Scenarios</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Travel photography needs</li>
            <li>Portrait and studio work</li>
            <li>Sports and action shooting</li>
            <li>Landscape and nature photography</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="eval-card">
          <h4>Ecosystem Considerations</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Available lens selection</li>
            <li>Accessory options and pricing</li>
            <li>Future upgrade paths</li>
            <li>Third-party support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="eval-card">
          <h4>Budget Planning</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Body cost vs lens investments</li>
            <li>Memory cards and batteries</li>
            <li>Editing software licensing</li>
            <li>Hidden maintenance expenses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Shopping Advice -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h3 class="guide-section-title">Practical Shopping Advice</h3>
      <div class="shopping-tips">
        <div class="tip-card highlight">
          <div class="tip-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/27574694/pexels-photo-27574694/free-photo-of-a-woman-taking-a-photo-with-her-camera.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" alt="Camera Research" />
          </div>
          <h4>Compare camera reviews</h4>
          <p>Read professional reviews, watch video comparisons, and prioritize hands-on testing. Online specs only tell part of the story - ergonomics matter significantly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3497126/pexels-photo-3497126.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" alt="New vs Used Cameras" />
          </div>
          <h4>New vs Used Considerations</h4>
          <p>Factor in warranty coverage and technology advancement pace. Camera bodies depreciate faster than lenses, making used lenses often excellent value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-image">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2929412/pexels-photo-2929412.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" alt="Camera Store" />
          </div>
          <h4>Retailer Selection</h4>
          <p>Choose authorized dealers over gray market imports. Warranty support and customer service are crucial for expensive camera equipment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

